From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NanoPi K1 Plus OpenWrt project <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] sunxi: keep K1 Plus Wi-Fi compatibility image LAN-first

The LAN-first recovery image keeps onboard Wi-Fi out of the active profile,
but the dedicated Wi-Fi compatibility branch still needs deterministic firstboot
management access. Hardware testing shows that asking rtl8189es to start hostapd
on the shared bridge during boot can wedge the network control path before the
wired address becomes reachable.

Add a board-specific uci-defaults helper that only activates when both the
RTL8189ES driver and hostapd userspace are present. Keep that image wired-first:
pin LAN directly to eth0 at 192.168.1.1 and let Wi-Fi stay opt-in after boot.
Recovery images keep their current behavior because they do not ship that Wi-Fi
stack.

---
 .../etc/uci-defaults/98-k1-plus-wifi-compat-lan      | 29 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+)
 create mode 100755 target/linux/sunxi/base-files/etc/uci-defaults/98-k1-plus-wifi-compat-lan

diff --git a/target/linux/sunxi/base-files/etc/uci-defaults/98-k1-plus-wifi-compat-lan b/target/linux/sunxi/base-files/etc/uci-defaults/98-k1-plus-wifi-compat-lan
new file mode 100755
index 000000000000..111111111111
--- /dev/null
+++ b/target/linux/sunxi/base-files/etc/uci-defaults/98-k1-plus-wifi-compat-lan
@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+#!/bin/sh
+
+. /lib/functions.sh
+
+[ "$(board_name)" = "friendlyelec,nanopi-k1-plus" ] || exit 0
+[ -f /etc/modules.d/rtl8189es ] || exit 0
+[ -x /usr/sbin/hostapd ] || exit 0
+
+ula_prefix="$(uci -q get network.globals.ula_prefix || true)"
+
+cat > /etc/config/network <<EOF
+config interface 'loopback'
+	option device 'lo'
+	option proto 'static'
+	list ipaddr '127.0.0.1/8'
+
+config globals 'globals'
+	option ula_prefix '${ula_prefix}'
+
+config interface 'lan'
+	option device 'eth0'
+	option proto 'static'
+	option ipaddr '192.168.1.1'
+	option netmask '255.255.255.0'
+	option ip6assign '60'
+EOF
+
+logger -t k1-plus "enabled Wi-Fi compatibility LAN-first policy on eth0"
+
+exit 0
